{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Existing featurebased XAI, on the other hand, focuses on 'what' image attributes or regions are more important to model decision function [71].",
    "As a result, it is critical to use human-centred approaches in understanding the rational aspect of AI explanation users.",
    "Human reasoning can simply explain what an object such as a 'apple' is by listing its higher-level properties such as 'Colour': red, 'Shape': round, whereas DNN, despite its significant performance, cannot explain its learned knowledge in a human-comprehensible manner [23].As a result, current feature-based explanation methods are still incapable of fully explaining the reason for model decision at a human-understandable level.",
    "They also do not correspond to high-level features such as concepts, which correspond to human thinking and reasoning.",
    "As a result, there is a need to provide human-readable interpretation methods that end-users, whether experts or decision-makers, can understand."
  ],
